This paper deals with the use of convolutional neural networks for automated chest x-ray predictions, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of natural language processing techniques for data preprocessing, which could potentially fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging and diagnosis, which could fall under the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category.
